<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
     BRAIN GYM FOR CHILDREN — UPDATED SECTION
═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section id="brain-gym" style="padding:80px 20px; background:linear-gradient(135deg,#f0f9ff 0%,#e8f5e9 100%);">
  <div style="max-width:960px; margin:0 auto;">

    <!-- ── BADGE + TITLE ── -->
    <div style="text-align:center; margin-bottom:48px;">
      <span style="background:#00b894; color:#fff; font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700;
                   padding:5px 14px; border-radius:20px; letter-spacing:1px; text-transform:uppercase;">
        🟢 Online Available
      </span>
      <h2 style="font-size:2.4rem; font-weight:800; color:#0d2b55; margin:16px 0 10px;">
        🧠 Awaken Your Child's <span style="color:#00b894;">Brain Power</span>
      </h2>
      <p style="font-size:1.1rem; color:#555; max-width:640px; margin:0 auto; line-height:1.7;">
        A scientifically structured cognitive workout for ages 6–15 — <strong>where learning becomes play,
        and play becomes growth.</strong> Available via live online video sessions globally.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- ════════════════════════════════
         BLOCK 1: WHAT IS BRAIN GYM?
    ════════════════════════════════ -->
    <div style="background:#fff; border-radius:16px; padding:36px; margin-bottom:32px;
                box-shadow:0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.07); border-left:5px solid #0d2b55;">
      <h3 style="font-size:1.5rem; color:#0d2b55; margin-bottom:12px;">🏋️ What is Brain Gym?</h3>
      <p style="color:#444; line-height:1.8; font-size:1rem;">
        Just like your body needs daily exercise to stay strong and healthy, <strong>your brain needs structured
        workouts to grow, focus, and perform at its peak.</strong> Brain Gym at Bhāva Tech is a scientifically
        designed program that trains memory, sharpens attention, builds problem-solving skills, and cultivates
        mindfulness — all tailored specifically for the developing child's brain aged 6–15.
      </p>
      <p style="color:#444; line-height:1.8; font-size:1rem; margin-top:12px;">
        The human brain is like a muscle — the more you engage it with the right exercises, the stronger,
        faster, and more creative it becomes. Our program activates both left brain (logic, language, math)
        and right brain (creativity, intuition, arts) functions simultaneously for <strong>whole-brain
        development.</strong>
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- ════════════════════════════════
         BLOCK 2: DISADVANTAGES OF NOT USING THE BRAIN
    ════════════════════════════════ -->
    <div style="background:#fff0f0; border-radius:16px; padding:36px; margin-bottom:32px;
                box-shadow:0 4px 20px rgba(220,53,69,0.08); border-left:5px solid #dc3545;">
      <h3 style="font-size:1.5rem; color:#c0392b; margin-bottom:8px;">⚠️ What Happens When the Brain is NOT Activated?</h3>
      <p style="color:#666; font-size:0.95rem; margin-bottom:24px; font-style:italic;">
        An unstimulated brain during childhood can lead to lasting challenges. Here's what science tells us:
      </p>
      <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(240px,1fr)); gap:16px;">

        <div style="background:#fff; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; border-top:3px solid #e74c3c;">
          <div style="font-size:2rem;">😴</div>
          <h4 style="color:#c0392b; margin:8px 0 6px;">Low Attention Span</h4>
          <p style="color:#555; font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.6;">Children struggle to focus for even 5 minutes, leading to incomplete tasks, poor academic performance, and classroom disruption.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="background:#fff; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; border-top:3px solid #e74c3c;">
          <div style="font-size:2rem;">🔇</div>
          <h4 style="color:#c0392b; margin:8px 0 6px;">Weak Memory Retention</h4>
          <p style="color:#555; font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.6;">Without memory training, children forget lessons quickly, repeat mistakes, and lack confidence during exams and recall tasks.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="background:#fff; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; border-top:3px solid #e74c3c;">
          <div style="font-size:2rem;">😤</div>
          <h4 style="color:#c0392b; margin:8px 0 6px;">Emotional Instability</h4>
          <p style="color:#555; font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.6;">An unstimulated prefrontal cortex leads to poor emotional regulation — frequent anger, anxiety, frustration, and social difficulties.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="background:#fff; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; border-top:3px solid #e74c3c;">
          <div style="font-size:2rem;">🧊</div>
          <h4 style="color:#c0392b; margin:8px 0 6px;">Suppressed Creativity</h4>
          <p style="color:#555; font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.6;">Right-brain dormancy blocks imagination, innovation, and artistic expression — essential skills for 21st century success.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="background:#fff; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; border-top:3px solid #e74c3c;">
          <div style="font-size:2rem;">📉</div>
          <h4 style="color:#c0392b; margin:8px 0 6px;">Slow Cognitive Growth</h4>
          <p style="color:#555; font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.6;">Unused neural pathways weaken over time. A brain with no structured stimulation develops fewer synaptic connections, slowing IQ growth.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="background:#fff; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; border-top:3px solid #e74c3c;">
          <div style="font-size:2rem;">📵</div>
          <h4 style="color:#c0392b; margin:8px 0 6px;">Screen Dependency</h4>
          <p style="color:#555; font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.6;">Passive screen consumption replaces active thinking, making the brain dependent on entertainment rather than generating its own ideas.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
